            <rationaleoptlist />
            <stem><![CDATA[<p style="">A student is writing an essay for his media class that addresses the question: Does the media report fairly or does it sometimes cross the line between reporting news and creating news? <span id="item_62381_TAG_7_BEGIN">Read</span> the paragraph from his essay. Then complete the task that follows.</p><p style=""><br />Does the media in today's society report fairly or does it cross a line between reporting the news and creating the news? We live in a world where news and entertainment are often the same thing, and in order to stay relevant and at the top of the <span id="item_62381_TAG_12" class="its-tag" data-tag="word" data-tag-boundary="start" data-word-index="1"></span>ratings scale<span class="its-tag" data-tag-ref="item_62381_TAG_12" data-tag-boundary="end"></span>, media outlets often find it necessary to <span id="item_62381_TAG_8_BEGIN">“create”</span> news that will draw the audience in, and, whether completely true or not, will make people talk. While most news stories are cemented in facts <span id="item_62381_TAG_9_BEGIN">and/or</span> actual occurrences, one only has to observe different news stations to see how very differently those stories are presented. A recent survey showed that <span id="item_62381_TAG_10_BEGIN">70%</span> of Americans do not trust the media and believe that, ultimately, most media outlets have an agenda: to be the first to report a story.</p><p style=""><br />The paragraph needs an appropriate conclusion. Click on the <span id="item_62381_TAG_11_BEGIN"><span style="font-weight:bold; ">best</span></span><span style="font-weight:bold; "> </span>concluding sentence from the following paragraph.</p><p style=""><br /><span class="interaction selectable" data-its-identifier="1" data-its-group="1"><span id="item_62381_TAG_1_BEGIN">All of this makes the average citizen question how he or she can <span id="item_62381_TAG_13" class="its-tag" data-tag="word" data-tag-boundary="start" data-word-index="2"></span>decipher<span class="its-tag" data-tag-ref="item_62381_TAG_13" data-tag-boundary="end"></span> what is fact and what is <span id="item_62381_TAG_14" class="its-tag" data-tag="word" data-tag-boundary="start" data-word-index="3"></span>embellished<span class="its-tag" data-tag-ref="item_62381_TAG_14" data-tag-boundary="end"></span> in the name of creating a <span id="item_62381_TAG_15" class="its-tag" data-tag="word" data-tag-boundary="start" data-word-index="4"></span>sensational<span class="its-tag" data-tag-ref="item_62381_TAG_15" data-tag-boundary="end"></span> story.</span></span> <span class="interaction selectable" data-its-identifier="2" data-its-group="1"><span id="item_62381_TAG_2_BEGIN">There are many contributing factors to what makes the public distrust media, but perhaps the most crucial is the type of news currently being reported.</span></span> <span class="interaction selectable" data-its-identifier="3" data-its-group="1"><span id="item_62381_TAG_3_BEGIN">Trust seems to be at the lowest point during political elections and at its highest during a national crisis.</span></span> <span class="interaction selectable" data-its-identifier="4" data-its-group="1"><span id="item_62381_TAG_4_BEGIN">Perhaps the lack of trust in media is a result of the constant <span id="item_62381_TAG_16" class="its-tag" data-tag="word" data-tag-boundary="start" data-word-index="5"></span>barrage<span class="its-tag" data-tag-ref="item_62381_TAG_16" data-tag-boundary="end"></span> of news we receive each day; there is no longer simply the morning and evening news, but there is constant access to news via television, computers, and phones.</span></span> <span class="interaction selectable" data-its-identifier="5" data-its-group="1"><span id="item_62381_TAG_5_BEGIN">Even when watching a current news story, a person is viewing a ticker at the bottom of the screen which provides even more information regarding various events.</span></span> <span class="interaction selectable" data-its-identifier="6" data-its-group="1"><span id="item_62381_TAG_6_BEGIN">All of this can be overwhelming and can lead to criticism since there is so much news available in so many different mediums.</span></span></p>]]></stem>
